A new era of crisis begins.
France and the rest of Europe are in the sights of investors.
A tornado statistics rose Tuesday on Europe.
Each of the states has published information relating to GDP 3A.
The Czech economy has stagnated this last quarter, while France and Germany are growing.
The bond market beats all records.
Investors look not only Italy but also Spain, France, Austria and others.
The offices of statistics in the euro area, Germany, Czech Republic and other European countries have published earlier their visions of economic development for the third quarter.
The GDP of Germany has forecast growth of 0.5 percent, that of France 0.4%.
The two countries have changed the data for the second quarter during which Germany is better placed than expected (growth of 0.3 percent instead of the 0.1 percent expected), however France reported a slight decrease of 0.1% (he was at the origin of stagnation).
The Czech economy has been a growth of 1.5 percent during the third quarter.
But the GDP has stagnated and according to the Bureau of the Czech statistical it is confirmed that we are moving towards a gradual reduction of economic growth.
The results were worse than analysts' forecasts.
The most important:
The Czech economic growth has been a 1.5% during the third quarter but has stagnated for the last quarter.
The German economy has been in the third quarter growth of 0.5% according to data provided and recalculated periodically.
The economy of the euro zone and the European Union has been a growth of 0.2% between July and September from the previous quarter, which corresponds to what analysts had expected.
The Greek economy fell 5.2 percent.
The yield on the 10-year bonds is 28,45 percent
Yields of the bonds of Spain and Italy are up to the limits.
The problems are beginning to feel in Austria, France, Belgium, etc...
The Czech bond yields continue to - below 4 percent while the situation worsens in the region.
Some voices in Germany to say that the ECB should be the guarantee of last instance.
