Iranian students are ready to die for their country's nuclear program.
They have created a human shield
A few hundreds of students graduate schools have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support by this gesture the nuclear programme of their countries face a possible Israeli attack.
The students went to pray at noon in front of the site and then called the death of the EU and Israel.
A few hundred students from the universities of Isfahan have created a human shield Tuesday around the Isfahan nuclear technology centre where uranium is transformed.
They have openly expressed they would defend the nuclear program of their countries, risking their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) found in its latest information that Iran has not stopped strengthening its nuclear weapons.
It was reported in Israel about a possible attack Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students went to pray at noon in front of the site and then called the death of the EU and Israel.
In the case of an attack, whose aim would be to destroy the Iranian nuclear program, the targets would be not only Isfahan, but also the Natanz site where is enriched uranium.
The feeding of a child obese: does not take breakfast and takes the deli for lunch
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 years have problems on weight, 9% of pupils are a weight in the - above the average and 5 percent are obese.
As the current research obese children come from families who have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important is the environment in which the human being and models that surround it.
On the tables of obese children is by example of the deli 50 percent more often than in the families of children with normal weight.
19% of obese had fries at the dinner, according to the survey conducted with an awareness "Obesity is not a chance"
In the families of small big sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15 percent said that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey on 900 children
The survey was conducted during the last school year and participated 900 students of primary schools of the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of the "Obesity is not a chance", supported by General Insurance and the company Unilever.
 Since the start is more than 12,000 students from sixth to third that project.
One of the factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children in on weight or obese, is the lack of proper food and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half the children interviewed indicated by example eat five times a day - breakfast, lunch, dinner, tea party, which is a basic principles of good nutrition," said one of the results of the investigation.
Without breakfast and dinner deli
Specialists draw attention to the fact that a healthy development takes a few basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23 percent of the families of pupils to eat my same hour.
In most families each takes his breakfast alone.
And the worst that has been raised is that a tenth of the population does not breakfast.
The breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The survey showed that in the families of the obese children consumes more often unhealthy fries.
Almost every pupil - not to mention weight – drink every day from sweetened drinks (70%).
More than 40% of children questioned the sport regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Bring you your diet
Another part of the investigation has allowed children chosen (204 172 boys and girls of 13 schools) to prepare its own food from options, according to their taste and their own personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children 12 to 15 years are far, in terms of a healthy diet, the ideal.".
Among their favourite meals there is a lot of cakes, meat and sweets.
"The more alarming is a large preference for sweet lemonades," is indicated in the survey results.
For lunch the pasta who took first place just before the white meat.
The children were not want starches and preference for fish and vegetable meal was very low.
Cape on health
The investigation has also shown that children are ready to change their habits from the time they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the session awareness" Obesity is not a chance ", there was a definite desire to move towards a healthy diet," the results of the investigation.
The most striking example was the sweetened lemonades because children have begun to give preference to water consumption.
The children were most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as a main dish and reduce the dishes and sugary "knedliky" (Czech speciality flour balls of bread or potatoes).
