How have evolved prices trips since 1989
Until 1989 there was in Czechoslovakia only 5 travel agencies of state: Cedok, Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autotourist.
The travel agencies offered trips at the time, especially in the countries of the socialist bloc, because the trips to the west were very limited.
The Czech tourists were traveling for the holidays in East Germany, Soviet Union (Sochi, Crimea and Black Sea), Bulgaria, Romania (both in the Black Sea) and Hungary (Balaton).
A great exception for the period from 1962 to 1972 when he was allowed to travel in Yugoslavia and the regime began to have a liking for the western and travel to Yugoslavia were very limited to the Czech tourists.
The great paradox of the socialist era, was that he was not authorized for the citizens of the socialist bloc (also for the Czechs) to travel individually even in the framework of the socialist countries.
In cases where the citizen Tchécoslovaque wanted to travel individually by example in Poland or in the Soviet Union he needed a letter of invitation or travel individual was not authorized.
The travel agencies at that time also provided trips to the West, however, he had to queue all night with a sleeping bag or have a "good knowledge" within the travel agency.
And even after it was not yet won.
The agreement for the currency was the condition to travel to the west was refused to people "politically incorrect" who couldn't travel.
The Czech currency was not however exchanged with others and it was not possible to obtain financial resources without the agreement of currencies (Western currency) for travel to the west.
The Czechs were the more often their holidays in the countries where there had therefore many houses and cottages that the Czechs are bought and this habit lasts until now.
The Czechs travel have known since 1989 a great revolution.
Although until 1989 the holidays in East Germany and Bulgaria were maximum, the Czechs have spent last year abroad 4 million vacation days in the countries of the world.
The great paradox which we have not aware today is that the most popular is Croatia where it was not possible to go free until 1989 as part of Yugoslavia.
The abolition of visas in the 1990s of the last century in neighbouring countries of the west have caused a huge wave of visits short-lived especially in Austria Vienna and Germany.
The Czechs could not long travel by plane to the west that everyone wanted to see at least a moment.
For example, in Paris the travel organisations were sleeping the Czechs in tents in parks because our income does not allow us to pay the hotel or a pension.
The typical feature of a trip of Czechs was winning with his own food, tinned sausage, etc... to save.
Another important moment was also the interchangeability of the Czech koruna which has enabled our tourists finally after dozens of years to freely buy the currency.
Our level of life as well as the average wage rose which caused around the year 1997 another important moment.
Thanks to a growing demand for travel travel agencies have begun since 1997 to prepare rounds with air charter service through contracts have tremendously reduced costs compared to what was there before.
In the late 1990s of the last century, the Czechs had links without visas with virtually most developed countries of the world to share the EU who later helped our trips.
Another interesting time in the history of tourism, when post-révolution was prepared the first air charter to a country exotic, Thailand, from the Czech Republic.
Since this year as each year of direct air charter take Czech tourists in the distant hot countries; this winter there will be 12 exotic destinations from the Czech Republic.
That is more than 100,000 Czechs who visit exotic countries each year.
Once an interesting time in this period which symbolizes our development post-révolution arrived in 2008.
November 17, 2008 the EU have abolished visas for Czech tourists and allowed our country to pull completely in the group of developed countries.
In 2008 the Czechs for the first time in history have spent more than half their holidays abroad (50, 3%) and for the first time in history have spent more than 15 000 crowns per person for a vacation abroad including charges annexes. crowns per person.
The General Assembly must find its President but this will be completed by a situation without solution "a pat"
Nearly 5mois already the Czech football is without President and there is a risk that the successor of Ivan Hasek at the head of the Association of Football of the Czech Republic is not yet known after a General Assembly to be held Thursday at Nymburk.
However there is still no agreement on what to vote to proceed.
Without this agreement, it is not possible to begin to vote for one of the three candidates.
Jindrich Rajchl, Miroslav Pelta and Tomas Paclik are interested in the direction of the Czech football.
Hasek resigned in June and during his departure has called on his colleagues has come together and find a strong personality who will lead the football in the future.
Only during the era after Hasek football returned back to differences between the chambers of the Association who cannot agree on a common candidate.
This is completely shown on 16 September when he had to choose a new president.
Delegates of the General Assembly gathered unnecessarily in the national House in Prague because the negotiations remained blocked and it has not even been issue to deal with how to elect.
There is no agreement on who has the right to vote in the General Assembly - only, it seems, the statutory representatives or the officials also have full powers.
In this single point there was a partial agreement since this moment with the help of the Bureau for the state and the right, according to which the representation on the basis of full power is not possible.
The differences continue always about the regulation for the election.
It is all too clear that the executive committee, which in its planned negotiation or extraordinary, has brought nothing to the situation
The opinions on the possibility of voting have changed several times but the underbelly remains the same.
The question is: how to proceed to the third round not to fall into the pat.
"The bone of contention is the following: either proceed according to the statutes or find another model," noted one of three vice-presidents of the Association of football of the Czech Republic Dusan Svoboda which represents professional football within the association.
According to the rules of the model expected wins in the third round that candidates who received the most votes in percentage within the Board for which he is a candidate.
The Moravia is prepared according to what is said to withdraw that wins the candidate who has received the highest percentage of votes in both chambers.
And the Czech side is studying the condition that the winner should have at least two thirds of the percentages of votes.
"Only this would then lose the idea of two previous rounds and this would completely deny the bicameral concept," said Svoboda which includes the objections of the Moravian part and that it would be better not to change the regulation and vote according to the statute in force.
It is surprising that Tomas Paclik also agreement even if he believes that the regulation of elections set according to the Pelta advantage among all the candidates.
"I want to vote according to the statutes of the association.".
"For that there has not yet insane ideas dreamt up by a representative as during the past General Assemblies," said the owner of Victoria Plzen who is a candidate for the first time and which in its submissions is defined mostly against Pelta.
Pelta remains optimistic.
According to him at Nymburk there will be a new President and believes that the candidates will cooperate in the future together and constructively.
"The qualification possible today in a European Championship should calm everyone.".
"Football on a wave of happiness and there will be more spirited for cooperation," the officer of Jablonec who among the three has the most experience leadership of both professional football at regional level.
Rajchl is more pessimistic.
"I believe in this agreement but unfortunately the situation is very tense.".
"This is not a problem between the Czechs and the Moravians, but there are tendencies to change the regulations to design.".
"This may cause a new blockage to the General Assembly.".
"I hope all good reason will win," said Rajchl.
There is not much time for a common agreement to all parties.
Some meetings should be held directly in Montenegro but who can say if the whole direction of football will be complete for the game.
The flight chartered in which to travel up to Podgorice between Vice other Dalibor Kucera and Rajchl, has not taken off for technical reasons and was seeking a variant to take part of the executive committee on the ground.
In the end it is the ministerial meeting, which could take place on Wednesday, which should be decisive.
The Minister of Education Youth and Sports Joseph Dobes would be very happy to receive the parties torn apart in the sports association the largest of the country and bring them to an agreement.
In the game, there are many: a state funding, the credibility of football and also the General Assembly of the Czech Union Sports who should determine the direction of Czech sport after the financial problems of Sazka.
