The bank scandal of Lake Zurich
The Bank the most adventurous of Europe is not in France or Italy, but in Switzerland.
The UBS has done almost bankrupt in the financial crisis and patina between - time from one crisis to another.
It is a German who must lead now.
This is certainly not what Axel Weber's "was imagined.
After his dramatic departure of the head of the Bundesbank; it was informed in July that it would post in 2013 an almost as dramatic: President of the Council of Administration of the big Swiss bank UBS - a big step towards a career unexpected and lucrative.
Axel Weber has said publicly praised; Switzerland for its beauty and UBS for its strength recently obtained and was kind of comments on the future colleagues.
"The UBS managed the Turnaround.".
"I welcome the collaboration with Kaspar Villiger and Oswald Grübel.".
And yet, as early as September it was clear that everything would change.
A securities dealer UBS in London had diverted all the security systems of the Bank and had soared about 1.7 billion euros.
The head of the board of the UBS Oswald Grübel, a banker well known not only in Switzerland, had to leave.
President of the board of directors of UBS is seen since as suffering - and all are asking: When Axel Weber finally amount?
We have already learned that Weber can be advised of the bank from February 2012.
And it will resume the presidency of administration already in May - not in 2013, as the bank statement Tuesday.
For Axel Weber it becomes difficult.
It is not a banker, a professor of economy and President of the bank, and he was certainly need a period of adjustment.
Suddenly he assumed responsibility for the strategy of a bank, which comes to prove yet again that she has long deserved the title of "the biggest bank scandal of Europe.".
Indeed, UBS is a huge side - until recently, it was the biggest asset manager of the world, and the other, it is faltering for years of a scandal.
Nothing, it seems, the Swiss bank savings so proud.
It started during the financial crisis.
Until 2007 UBS had an excellent reputation.
The image of the Swiss asset manager of strong, silent and cunning, but also, she had combined with ambitious objectives: it also wanted to become, in the field of investment banking, a very large bank.
So the UBS managed to one side in 2007 with 1.6 billion more money from a wealthy clientele than any other bank in the world.
On the other hand, she had advanced as investment bank in the league of the world's largest banks.
That made sense.
The former banker Hans Geiger and later a professor of bank for long years in Zurich said: "I have always taken the UBS as a model of good bank before my students."
"In the current context, one wonders: how I could simply be wrong at this point?"
It is profoundly wrong.
In 2007 it emerged that for the first time something was amiss at UBS.
In the middle of the year, President Peter Wuffli withdrew surprisingly, which was regarded until - there as a senior and a brilliant intellectual banker.
A few months later was tipped for what reasons he was party.
The division of the bank had soared with Only documents and has done a cross on billions.
To support this, the UBS announced a capital increase of $13 billion francs and made a cross.
For this she did find investors, but who, shortly before, have a role player furrowed her brow: Asian state not - transparent from Singapore and an Arab state, which was passed over in silence, to the point that there has never learned his name.
"This was the first time.
In April 2008 has worsened.
The bank was to announce fresh losses running into billions, the chairman of the board of directors Marcel Ospel, who was still in 2006 the second board the better paid to Switzerland, withdrew.
In October 2008 the disaster followed: the UBS was given its investment mistakes in the financial crisis before the bankruptcy and had to be rescued by the state.
The national bank bought at UBS tens of billions of securities issues, the Swiss Confederation gave six billion francs for convertible bonds, for which it could become a co-owner of the bank.
Any Switzerland has been rocked - because she noted how it can be dramatic for a small country, harboring if big banks.
Finally, the balance sheet total of the UBS 2007's "raised more than five times the economic performance of Switzerland (see chart).
"We have not been able to save the UBS again," said the researcher of banks, Geiger.
After the first disaster in the second.
Already a few months before, UBS had surrendered because of a tax dispute with America and is ready to publish the data of the wealthy clientele, who had defrauded the IRS perhaps with the help of the Bank.
In addition, it accepted a payment of 780 million - in repayment of unjustified profits from these operations with a fine together.
Thus the UBS has more or less published that she had helped to tax fraud.
At the same time she lost something that has always been its capital in competition with the rich clients: the prestige of the discretion.
After the scandal Swiss banking secrecy has not been the same.
It was followed by the withdrawal of the head of the board and the chairman of the board of directors.
And the exodus of clients' money.
Thus the bank had lost in a few months its credibility in both sectors of business: investment banking because of bad speculation and asset management because of tax fraud.
And, as there was somewhat of a return to calm, and as we thought, that UBS would do, he followed this unfortunate history of merchants of title: one merchant rocketing title 1.7 billion euros before the bank realization that something was amiss.
And it publishes: with risk management in the investment bank that still does not seem to work.
"With the case Adoboli, risk control to too little changed," said Martin Janssen, an economist and professor of finance at the Institute of the University of Zurich.
The financial director of a large German bank is safe: "the problem of UBS is that it has no control of the risks."
However it was exactly the idea of caution, with which the Swiss bankers had long taken their function to become guardian of the great fortune of the world: not too great risks, but safety for money - and the world could well collapse in the - beyond the Alpine republic.
The treasures of Swiss banks had become the symbol of an unshakeable reliability as Lindt & amp; Spruengli chocolate are for a particularly noble.
The central UBS in Zurich will still hand in hand with the strong cliché of the private Swiss bank - it is only a little more.
Already the situation is classic.
The Bank has its headquarters in the central train station of Zurich, which led directly to the central train station in Lake Zurich, which itself is surrounded by the snow-capped mountains of Switzerland.
The buildings here are prestigious, rents stores are among the highest in Europe.
The bijoutiers as Tiffany's, it is here between stores Swiss traditions like confectionery amp; Spruengli.
For centuries of Swiss bankers have resided here: the national bank through the palace of Credit Suisse until private banks elitist as Julius Bär.
It arrives in the lobby of the UBS by a heavy door.
Inside, the walls are clad in stone, before are thick leather chairs, and the logo of the bank, a major label for "safe.".
The UBS knows what the client research here: security.
This idea of the Swiss bank has a day off the market - or betrayed the two big Swiss banks, UBS and Credit Suisse, as the head of a small Swiss private bank.
He would prefer not to read his name in the newspaper, finally as all Swiss bankers it does business with the two big banks.
The UBS would become too large, it is - - especially in investment banking, where the Anglo-Saxons are also common.
The Swiss there would have nothing more to say.
"And even when they have long adapted to the mores of the Anglo-Saxons."
This has been the Anglo-Saxon investment bank UBS, which has changed, it has made high profits and then the debacle: no European financial institution has lost so much money in the jungle of sub-prime mortgage loans as the big Swiss bank.
The disaster became apparent on 15 October 2008.
"This Wednesday the coalition government of the small country of seven million inhabitants has undertaken the largest rescue operation in the history of their nation," wrote author Lukas Hässig in his book "The crash of the UBS.".
With up to 68 billion francs about 45 billion euros, politicians have agreed to save the bankrupt the big bank.
How could this happen?
If we speak with Swiss bankers, they see the problem, especially to the size of UBS.
In June 1998, two of the three major Swiss banks have found a huge group.
A bank has been created, which was already too big for the small Swiss - and constantly recorded an increase.
What has helped is that the two banks prédécesseuses different from UBS were completed: a bank rich, but lethargy with strong asset management in Zurich and a poorer, but already more internationalized.
Suddenly, the international investment banks have been favourably access to a lot of money, with which they were able to turn a huge wheel.
Two names are associated with the rise of UBS: Peter Wuffli, from 2001 to 2007 Head of Group UBS, and Marcel Ospel, formerly chairman of the board of directors.
"I always thought that Wuffli and Ospel constituted a dream team," said the researcher of banks, Hans Geiger.
"Wuffli, the great intellectual modest, which are very well models and statistics, and Ospel, the intuitive, who made his way up to the summit with the learning of the bank."
But Ospel would have relied until "at the end to Wuffli.
And Wuffli would probably have committed to the end a decisive error: "He thought that its models were the reality," said Geiger.
"This is a tragic fall."
Disastrous, perhaps.
One thing is clear: the exuberance arrived before the fall.
The staff of the UBS remembers clearly rallies leaders during which the head of the group Wuffli gave always the same: to dethrone Goldman Sachs.
The US bank was the most powerful investment bank in the world.
She has ordered the "League Tables" the rankings, which have documented at this time the success of the banks.
After all the UBS wanted to climb to the top.
Some steps have already succeeded.
In case of currency and transactions in securities it has played a very important role.
