The smart crows spread in cities
In many places, freux are considered "problem of birds." But experts say that these highly intelligent animals are no longer hunt cities for a long time.
Some, like the others want to get rid of them as quickly as possible. The crows belong to the city for centuries, but in many communities, residents' complaints are increasing because of the dirt and noise of animals.
A antidote against "No problem of birds" is not yet in sight.
In the first ostfriesisch symposium on crows, experts have said that this is no longer possible to drive the freux cities.
Experts from across Germany deliberated on possible solutions.
They are looking for alternatives in cities
The protectors of nature based the problems of cities on the exodus of freux particularly protected: The use of chemicals in agriculture to destroy more of the traditional vital spaces.
Hunting, development and the slaughter of nesting trees typical made life difficult for birds.
The crows are under the protection of nature.
There are large settlements with more than 600 nesting couples in the westfälischen Soest, in the north west - including Jever, and Achim Diepholz near Bremen and in Leer.
In 2005, a controversial project had earned negative ads because of the massacre of crows in this region.
Critics have found the capture of birds in traps and their killing with clubs particularly brutal.
"The normal expulsion, the exclusion serves to nothing," said the planner of the city and the landscape of Leer, Werner Klöver.
The destruction of nests using the water under pressure or cut down trees, often produces undesirable consequences, said the environmental expert Manfred Kaiser of Lahr.
"The animals moving away, large colonies split up and they disperse in other places."
"The elimination is conceivable that in exceptional cases such as hospitals, retirement homes or schools.
"We are forced to live with them, we cannot be exterminated."
The problem is not solved in the cities without the inclusion of the periphery, according to the opinion of the mayor Wolfgang Kellner of Leer.
Concevable is a combination of the ousting of animals to a aversif conditioning and tempting offers to help resettle elsewhere.
Psychologist and ethnologist, Maria Jürgens Uta prospectait "signs info in place of chainsaws" to establish relations with completely different: "We can finally better bear a button in the face with a dose of self-confidence."
Jürgens co-founded the Ascheberger - road - educational dimensions of the Schleswig Holstein -, road signs advising on the lives of these freux very intelligent.
This project was between - time adopted by tourists.
Jürgen gave his own opinion about the critical of the noise caused by birds: "This is a large number of communication, these birds - there have much to say.".
The intelligence and the ability of animals are legendary: The freux are not only work instruments to achieve a treat but they make their own tools as instruments of work.
The éthologistes of Cambridge University tested four freux recently, at what point is the intelligence of the birds.
In one experiment, the birds quickly learned that they had to do down scaffolding with stones in order to achieve a larva.
Without much training, they recognized that a déterminément stone should have some size and form to collapse the platform.
In a second trial, the astute crows then had to solve a problem more compact.
In a cylinder placed vertically, researchers had placed a small bucket with a larva.
The birds could not reach their spoils with their spat.
However, the researchers had set pieces of wire at their disposal.
All four animals formed a hook with which they fished the small bucket of small pipe.
Three of the four freux manage even from the start.
