The legal firm Clement of Bancroft PLLC, was part of the two dozen firms that helped sponsor the annual dinner of the Federalist Society (Fédéraliste), a group of dedicated to defend the longtime conservative legal principles.
Another firm that sponsored the dinner, Jones Day, represents one of the trade associations that have challenged the law, the National Federation of Independent Business (National Federation of Independent Business).
Another sponsor was the pharmaceutical giant Pfizer Inc, which presents a huge financial stake in the outcome of the dispute.
The dinner was held at a Washington hotel a few hours after the conference of the court on the case.
If there was, among other top Republican, Mitch McConnell, the Senate and opponent of the health care bill.
The star guests at the dinner? Scalia and Thomas.
This is not new: the two judges were present to the events of the Fédéraliste Society for years.
And there was nothing that goes against the rules of ethics.
In fact, the judges are exempt from the code of conduct that governs the actions of federal judges.
If they were, they probably by the TSE Code of Canon 4C, which states: "A judge can attend fundraising organizations related to the right and although the judge could not be a speaker, a guest of honour, or appearing on the program of such an event.".
Nevertheless, the mere presence of Scalia and Thomas near two law firms of the case, as well as a business with a massive financial interest, was enough to alarm the activists of ethical government.
"This violation of ethics and superb indifference to the code contradicts the statements of several judges that the Court respect the same rules apply to all other federal judges," said Bob Edgar, president of Common Cause.
"The judges drank and ate and a gala fundraiser with lawyers who have cases pending before the court.".
Their presence and their participation in the collection of funds of this event to dismantle any claim to impartiality, and is unacceptable.
Scalia and Thomas have shown little regard for the critics saying that they mix too easily the affairs of the court with the agenda of groups such as the Fédéraliste Society.
And the wife, Ginni Thomas, is a conservative activist haut-profil.
Moreover, the Tories claim that it is the judge Elena Kagan, who has an ethical problem, and not Scalia and Thomas.
Kagan was solicitor general of the Obama administration when the first opposition to the law have been brought in the court of first instance.
His critics have been pressing for Kagan has recused to hear the case, saying it was too invested in the defense of the law to be impartial.
Kagan gave no indication that it would.
