The decline in economic activity generated, until November, a steady rise in unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography the state's unemployment rate during the first three quarters of the year there has been a rise accelerated, because during the January to March 55 000 053 sinaloens were unemployed, with a rate of 4.53 percent Population Economics Active, in the second quarter the rate became 5.28 percent and the July to September the average has continued to raise up to 6.19 percent, a rate that represents more than 74 000 sinaloens unemployed, an increase from the first half of 18 000 969 people.
Less liquidity
The Sinaloa unemployment during the year is multifactoriel, according to the economist Gerardo López Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Social and Economic Sciences of the UAS, rising unemployment can be explained indirectly on the actions carried out by public policy.
"What we see is a rise in unemployment, which is due to various factors, among which the loss of liquidity on the market due to a restriction of resources by the legislation approved in Congress to fight money laundering, because for people who earn dollars an illegal way is not easy as they work for the win, they use and invest in something," he says.
Migration held
López Cervantes reported that rising unemployment is also due to a demographic factor.
"The number of people leaving the state to go to work abroad, the United States has been restricted, first because of the difficulties of entry and secondly because as they have already struggling to find work, these people remain here and ask for sources of work, unemployment," said déclaré-t-il.
Lack of serious
The analysis of the labour market sinaloen worsens in considering the high level of lack of seriousness that predominates between working conditions, according to the INEGI, the 60,38 percent of the working population in this state is working without pay as worker with no social insurance institution.
In part of unemployment and the lack of seriousness, another reason for the discrepancy are low wages, the entity has the lowest salaries, according to the records of the Mexican Institute of Social Insurance and the Secretariat of Labor and Social forecast.
The average monthly earnings of workers sinaloens was, until September, 5 000 352 pesos, well below the national average, which stands at 7 thousand 375 pesos.
Contraction of FDI
As part of the decline in economic activity and rising unemployment, in 2011 we recorded the biggest reduction of Foreign Direct Investment last 10 years, according to the Secretariat of Economy from January to June the IED the state has reached 630 697 thousand dollars, representing a decline of 87.74 percent compared to the 143 000 312 5 million dollars registered in the same period the previous year.
In turn, the Secretariat of Economic Development of the Government of the State for a total investment of 17,280 trillion pesos per year, recorded mainly by the companies of the service sector.
The debt
Given the scenario of economic contraction, the Government of the State requested in July at the congress public approval of a credit of $3 trillion pesos, intended to investment in infrastructure projects in the 18 municipes, with the aim of reactivating the economy, the approval of the Congress of the State has been to 2,600 trillion pesos and until November there was no benefit in any sector of the economy of the state.
Reactions
For the representatives of the sector employers, the first year of Government of Mario López Valdés demonstrates a lack of management capacity of the Government.
Miguel Loredo López, president of the National Chamber of Transformation, said that in 2011 there was not a harmonisation of the wishes of the various sectors - included, the Government of the State.
"The performance of the economy of Sinaloa during this year was really very poor, we must work hard to recover the ground we have lost this year, in 2012 we must double our effort, he took up the effort of all and especially the synchronized already this new team of Government, hope that next year is much better," he says.
Economic Sluggishness
Loredo López said that events like the frozen the beginning of the year have held the state's economy and restricted his performance and growth.
"The low economic fluxe is product of several events, between which the frosts, one of the main effects has been a slow economy which is fast enough to generate economic dynamism that allows an acceptable level e flow in the trial, products and services and therefore, at the end of the year we close to - much below the expectations we had," he said.
Redefine the vocation
For Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, president of the Patronale Confederation of the Sinaloa Mexican Republic said that it wants to harness the state towards productive activities more dynamism.
"In general terms we have observed that we worked, we believe that it is necessary to develop a long-term programme which redefined the vocation and the economic direction of the state, because it is important that all the potential out material and human resources of Sinaloa," he said.
Many to do
The president of the Coparmex stressed the importance of establishing a vision of the future which channels the best efforts of the Government.
"In general terms, I would say that the Government has made efforts to give good results in different areas, in terms of economic development a few advances, but it is important to develop a long-term programma," he said.
He pointed out that the current administration has shown advances in the way of management of public policy.
"There are elements that allow us to say that the Government is more inclusive, I can say is that we have worked a lot and the Government is aware of the fact that there is still much to do," he said.
Sentenced to 8 kilograms of marihuana
A person resident in Novolato was sentenced to five years in prison and a fine of 100 days for possession of eight kilograms of marihuana.
The Prosecutor General of the Republic has informed that the small trafficker sentenced is Omar Alexis Valenzuela Sandoval, for crimes against health, in its variant of possession of marijuana for sale.
According to the AP / file SIN / CLN / 687 / 2010 / M - I, Valenzuela Sandoval was arrested by agents of the Mexican Army on 7 June 2010 during a surveillance operation in the street Cipriano Valdez, before the number 80 in El Castillo, Navolato.
The small dealer driving in a van type pick - up, white, in which he was carrying a black bag in the luggage door - the vehicle and the co-pilot a small backpack where the military found eight kilograms and 23 grams of marihuana.
For this reason, the items confiscated were available to the Second District Judge and sentenced is still in the Centre of Performing Legal Consequences of Offences.
The financial obligations towards the contributions to the books
The works of contemplés in social programs like Hábitat, Públicos and 3x1 Rescate of Espacios para migrants may not be finished recording where serious delays due to the lack of economic resources, said Miguel Ángel López Miranda.
The director of Municipal Social Development said that although so far the construction programs have progressed, they find themselves in a situation of risk, because the Government of the state has not fulfilled its obligations to provide contributions that exceed the 11 million pesos in the three programmes.
It reported that in total, the investment of these three programmes is approximately 50 million pesos, which the state must provide the 25 percent and so far only the Federation and the Municipe have provided resources for the books, therefore there is the possibility of a delay in their completion.
"They must provide a contribution of 12 million and despite the fact that the year will soon finish they have given nothing, even if since July they should give us a party," he says, "and we, for not registering delays, we started the works and we have a lot of progress, but we need the money.".
He mentioned that last year, during the administration of Jesús Aguilar Padilla, the state had not paid the corresponding contributions, therefore at the beginning of the administration the Municipe had to seek a credit to cover 7 million that the administration of the state had not provided this opportunity - there.
"We had already suffered in the previous sexennal period because the State did not have the economic ability to participate and programmes continue to function and this year we, to have access to these programs, we get the resources to cover what the state had not paid," détailla-t-il.
Despite the fact that there is a commitment from the authorities of the state to provide these resources, he said that they had asked the Secretary of Administration and Finance, Armando Villarreal, to activate management for the corresponding percentages arrive as soon as possible.
"They must provide almost 12 million and despite the fact that the year will soon end, they have given nothing.".
The Court valid "analogue switch-off in 2015" in Mexico
The substitution of analogue know her by the exchange is a more important that the world has suffered the last few years
The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional controversy that the Senate and the House of Deputies made against the presidential decree which advance the so-called "analog" cut 2021 to 2015, as the eight votes needed to invalidate have not been met.
A minority of four ministers - included, the President of the Court, Juan Silva Meza, considered that President Felipe Calderón has not exceeded his powers when he issued the decree detailing the actions to make the transition to digital television.
With this result, the constitutional controversy promoted by the Senate of the Republic, was dismissed for not having reached the qualified majority of eight votes for the Court to rule on the constitutionality or not - constitutionality of decree, and this continues to be in force.
The draft sentence, developed by the Minister Olga Sanchez Cordero, suggested the statement of the decree as not - constitutional, due to the fact that the regulation on radio and television is an award reserved by law to the Federal Telecommunications Commission (Cofetel), in contravention of the principles of command and subordination of law.
In favour of the project voted only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies have promoted two constitutional controversies to challenge the decree and admitting complaints, the Minister Sánchez Cordero has suspended the application of the decree and all actions planned by it for the digital transition.
The plenary session of ministers resolved an attempt by the complaint made by the Chamber of Deputies, without discussing the project with the Minister Sánchez Cordero is also responsible.
In his speech, the president said he did not agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the Federal Executive may not structure through general standards the measures for the public administration is preparing.
"I believe that if he did it would affect the autonomy of the regulatory body," and he recalled that the planning of public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of the federal executive, which has for constitutional mandate the leadership of the state.
The substitution of analogue know by digital know is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered the last few years and this is reflected in a better exploitation of the radio spectrum, signal a better quality and more channels.
Ajourner change, he argued, would be that the benefits of the digitisation that involves a decision of public interest that not only has a technical dimension, "because it also includes economic issues, social, political and national security.".
These questions, he said, "require the operation of a system, in accordance with the principle of economic direction of the state, includes a group of powers that the Constitution grants the faculty of the Executive of the State".
He recalled that a large number of countries across the world have already finished the digital transition and they have done through the Executive, despite the fact that they had strong technical bodies.
We cannot conclude that the Commission, in issuing the decree, has invaded a form the sphere of competence of Congress, because it provides in the administrative sphere respect laws issued by the Législative, assura-t-il.
The analysis of the possibility of a "vote by vote count" in Michoacán
According to the data highlighted by PREP, the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 6 thousand 74 trial - verbal totals.
The possibility of the count "vote by vote" is a reality in relation to the electoral trial this year in Michoacán, where according to the data highlighted by the Préliminaires Électoraux Results Program (PREP) the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 6 thousand 74 trial - verbal totals.
In this sense, the president of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (EIM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, the past 9 November, the electoral body has approved a series of guidelines to harmonise standards to the federal reform.
It is recalled that Michoacán has not licensed nor its Constitution Policy or his or her State Electoral Code Act, Justice Électorale, at the same time that the Congress of the State approved the reforms that will shortly before the legal time limit for that electoral trial can enter into force and the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel failed its publication in the deadlines set by the Act of the Official Journal of the state, with the argument that he had some objections.
The 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) has resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Législative Power and described as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the representative of the state for constitutional reform, because it has no right to "sanction or challenge.".
Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote," María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the relevant guidelines by the General Council of EIM it will be possible to achieve the total and partial counting of votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial tally of votes, or several electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the trial - coincide verbal; there was no trial - of voting and counting in the case of the ballot box is not among the president; or there are obvious errors or defects trial - verbal.
Moreover, the total count of votes received in all polls of the election will be done when there is an index of the fact that the difference between the candidate supposed respective winner of the election and which won second place in the poll is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session is express a petition of the representative of the party and / or coalition who presented the second candidates reported.
The total count can also be achieved if at the end of the common count it follows that the difference between the candidate assumed winner and second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the petition specific political party whose candidate came second, cases in which we exclude electoral packages that have been subject of the partial tally.
It should be noted that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where the PREP, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of 923 trial - verbal totals.
His last wish
His ashes will be prevalent in the Sierra of Zapalinamé, confirms the family.
The remains of the pilot Felipe Bacio Cortés will arrive in Saltillo, his hometown, this Sunday night and Monday people will present their tributes and there will be a misse of requiem.
According to his family, the last will of Lt. Colonel - was that his ashes be spread in the Sierra of Zapalinamé.
After receiving the tributes to the other people died in the accident, the family of Bacio Cortés returned to the capital of Coahuila on a Forces aircraft Mexico Aériennes, the closest attended the ceremony at Campo Maret.
At noon the ashes of Lieutenant Colonel - arrived at the chapel of vigil the boulevard Nazario Ortiz Garza, where the family and friends.
At 17: 30 hours, he was present tributes to the Technological Institute of Saltillo organised by his former colleagues technological BA and American football team including Felipe Bacio when he was preparing for the bachelor's degree.
"He wanted to go back to Saltillo and that his ashes be spread in the Sierra of Zapalinamé, he has always said it" has his family and friends, "said Sandra Bacio Cortés, sister of the pilot.
For her, Lieutenant Colonel - had done all his dreams, it considers that it was in the fullness of his life, "he had success, he was a father and son, extraordinary, a loving brother and treated much his family.".
Felipe Bacio Cortés abandoned very young city of Saltillo to register at the College of the Air in Zapopán, Jalisco.
Some couldn't believe it, because they said it had even bad truck; but he has always followed his dream of becoming a pilot.
His nephew, Jorge Alberto Dávila Bacio remembers that it was a very good person, "when he was in Saltillo all the family wanted to greet him, as was the occasion in which he has made Martha Sahagún in Saltillo.".
The young man even remembers that when he was 7 years he has traveled to Zapopán for the graduation of its parent, for that he knows that his uncle is died doing what he loved most in life: fly an aircraft.
His last farewell
With honors we said goodbye to Air Force Lieutenant Colonel Mexican Felipe Bacio Cortés, tribute which took to head the governor Jorge Torres López, presented by the people and the Government of the State, the Mexican Army, through the Sixth Military Zone, Air Force, Mexican directors and students at the Technological Institute of Saltillo, where he studied in 1985 and distinguished himself in both studies as in sport.
Bacio Cortés died recently when the helicopter he was piloting crashed, to the Secretary of the Government, Jose Francisco Blake Mora and another six people, all officials of the service.
The remains of the pilot Bacio Cortés born in Saltillo arrived (incinerated) at 18: 05 hours to be handed over by the funeral to members of the Air Force Center, led by Major Jaime Martinez, on the esplanade of the group, where he was expected by his family - included his daughter, Amanda and his wife Cristina, his mother, his brothers and his parents, students and teachers.
