Quinteto has included the country in turn to celebrate two decades of trajectory
"" Going to Costa Rica is a dream that became reality "
In the exclusive interview with Viva, bassist Jeff Ament, Pearl Jam, said that the group is prepared to offer one of his best concerts the next Sunday on the National Stadium.
They waited more than 20 years, but the group said that for them it will also be a dream to occur in this country.
It is the founding member and bassist Jeff Ament said, speaking exclusively with Viva, Brazil, last week.
The group is in the south wing of his tour - American celebration of two decades of work and Sunday 20 will only stop in Central America.
This day - there will be on the National Stadium, from 19: 30 hours next to the group of Los Angeles The X and national Las Robertas.
This is an excerpt of the conversation, whose full transcript is in La Nacion on the Internet.
For its costariciens followers, the fact that Pearl Jam will happen in Costa Rica is a dream become reality. Are you aware of what your fans live?
Going to Costa Rica is a dream that became reality for us.
This is our second time in the Central and South America and so far this has been awesome.
I spent in Costa Rica only once the holidays; it is a country so beautiful and I think we can spend a few days.
This émotionne to bring our music - low.
I ask you, because there is a kind of devotion to the group, the fans live with intensity the previous days.
What is your message to your most ardent followers?
Thank you stay beside us for all these years.
There have been 21 years for us to reach Costa Rica; thank you for having waited and we are sorry that so much time had to spend up to the concert.
Some people say that his show is the largest of the year.
Is it adds a little pressure to your visit.
Some of the biggest shows that we have offered during the last 21 years have taken place in the last two weeks.
We have offered a two huge shows in Sao Paolo and we hope that this has put us in shape for this concert in Costa Rica.
We are very eager to produce.
We love this country, we like to do the surfing and jungle; for two things, Costa Rica is one of the best countries in the world.
How did you discovered Costa Rica and waves for surfing?
We have a lot of friends surfers and I have a very good friend who lives in Colima and the waves are incredible here - low.
My friends would always make the surf in Costa Rica and Nicaragua, side of Mexico, are great places to make the surfing; it is as we have learned, through the people who love snowboarding.
Seeing the tour, you have offered huge shows, with a lot of songs.
What have you planned for your presentation to Costa Rica?
As we never products - low, we have no restrictions on what we can do.
We will try to do the best show possible, with a wide variety of songs; we will try to interpret two songs from each album and offer our fans a good repertoire and various.
You never repeat the repertoire.
What is this?
I believe that this is partly because we have nine discs and we can interpret more than 120 songs and each love songs different, so it is very difficult to choose which songs interpret each evening.
When we have two or three songs in the pool that we have not seen for a very long time, that helps us to stay focused and surprises us because it reminds us of the reasons why we loved these songs and we can have forgotten.
That fact that the show is more interesting for us, and therefore I think it is also becoming more interesting for people.
With this tour, you are celebrating 20 years of trajectory.
Looking back, it is difficult to believe everything you succeeded?
Yes, absolutely.
In the first place, I believe that none of us had imagined that we would form a large rock group, and the fact that we have done for more than 20 years that it seems a dream.
We continue to tell our blessings and to continue to make music together we émotionne a lot.
We love and we love create music.
We are lucky to go to places of the world that we have always wanted to go.
Things could get better for us.
That means for you to have been a fundamental element in the creation of the grunge?
This has always been an honour for us to form part of this group of large groups.
We are friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It is surprising when a movement arises from a group of friends and is very common.
From time to time, a group comes to a city, but it is much more strange when five or ten groups out at the same time in the same city.
We are proud and it is an honour for us to form part of the group of Seattle.
We are playing with some of them from time to time.
Last year we participated in a festival with Alice in Chains and we have been in Canada with Mudhoney, Soundgarden we have seen in their tour, so we are lucky to still be friends with all of them and it is an honour for us to form part of his of Seattle that arises.
It is also very strange that a group like the your remains united and with the same members for a long time.
Yes, four of us have been together for 21 years and Matt (Cameron) has joined 13 years ago, and only it is much more time than many groups normally last.
In the first place, I believe that we are all lucky to be alive, and second, we are all concerned for the other.
We are all friends and through this there are musical boulevards that give freedom to experiment.
We have confidence in each other with the music and it could only get better.
Your relationship with the word celebrity has not been easy; however, thanks to your success, you could do what you want.
How do you find a balance?
As we grew up, it was easier for us to find a balance.
We ensure that we do not spend too much time on tour because it is easy to fall in this game of big numbers and people who like your music.
If we do not forget that people are there for the music, it helps us not forget that it must respect the music and what has made, set in mind the fact that there is famous and a rock star, which is not really any of us.
How do you remember your other project, Mother Love Bone?
I think we've written good songs and the beginning this was awesome.
We were a group for almost three years and we have not released a new album before the death of Andy (Andrew Woods).
There was a lot of frustrations for the fact that it lasted so little and the most important is the fact that we are still very friends with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore) that began in the group with us and when I listen to a song or I see a picture I think of the incredible person that Andy was and how it was making me laugh, it was always a pleasure to work, laugh, talk about music, football and many other things with him.
It was a human being surprising and we lack.
The national group Las Robertas will open the show in Costa Rica.
It is true that you know his work, especially Eddie Vedder and for that you have chosen for the opening?
Yes, the production has sent us videos with various proposals and that - there was the group that we liked the most, so we are eager to see what Las Robertas can offer direct and this must be very distracting.
What you always change the words of Yello Ledbetter live?
It is a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), so I don't know.
It is he who sings and I believe it does with the first words he imagines.
As bassist, what are its influences?
There are both...
Among the first I remember there was Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone Place, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many influences, that I could talk all the after noon on the Baathists - that I love.
How managed Pearl Jam has maintain the grunge despite the fact that it is no longer in fashion?
I believe that we all feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think, it reminds me of the groups that I mentioned, as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those who have emerged at the same time and, if it is in now, I think it is wonderful, because it is a music that is worth the trouble to listen and groups like Mudhoney are now the best music ever.
At the beginning, his music had a more obscure content and now it has become more positive.
What should this change?
It is interesting, because I believe that there are songs in the new album that seem lighter, but there are also songs, as The End gold Just Breathe qualified as very obscure songs, even if those - it can sound a little positive.
With the two, when Ed has played for me, I cried when I listened to and those - these are songs deeply obscure.
I think if you grow up and there was a trauma in your life and you lose a parent or friend, these things are starting to influence your art and your music and songs, without doubt, is it for me.
I also think that we can also be happy and even as it can make music.
