Parc or mountain?
The architects coincide on the opportunity of the convening the - beyond the controversy over the fees
The municipal competition on the 16 doors opens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
By the middle of the 1980s, at the height of the already extinct - Metropolitan Corporation of Barcelona (CMB), this Administration has printed posters promoting Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as the biggest park in the metropolitan Barcelona.
Moreover, it also contained a comparison, in figures, with the New York's Central Park.
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park became again, in the imagination of many people, the higher limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital is the only one who is not heading on the axis north – south, if not high (low) - (sea).
The classification of Collserola as natural park is to the advantage of this idea.
The reference was not Central Park or Yellowstone, with boar in the role of the bear Yogi.
This was the situation until, in September, the mayor convened a mega - competition composed by 16 competition for all the doors of access to Collserola.
A door to the idea of park, no doubt.
That is, or someone wants to put doors on the field.
The question appears alone: Collserola: park or mountain?
The competition, both in terms of its organisation as regards the reflection on the city is a topic of conversation all the architects of Barcelona.
It is almost a recurring theme, including two former members of that caste elected to speak when they recognize in an elevator.
And this is just one of the few opinions on which coincide three architects of Barcelona, university professors, who are presented.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the competition is appropriate.
For Roldán, after the coastal front "it is necessary to" discuss "the mountain front" because the speech Ildefons Cerda, green blocks has not been led to end.
"It must start from the basis that the park more extended Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things for its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex, "gave the verdict the architect for which the title of" Collserola "contains a" trap "lexicon: we must think about those - it" as access to a park, but the delimitation of some areas in which it must act. ".
Modol, as Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, described the proposal as "intellectual challenge" with "some peril.".
There are perils of "the uncertainty of projecting public space" after the experience in the 1980s and has been in the area of the Forum, "his swan song.".
The first fear is the demarcation of borders on which we can build.
"Limiting something means making the next step," i.e., the excess.
"We must think about new instruments, urban planning, because the current [in reference to the Metropolitan General Plan (MGP)] can cause genuine disasters.".
By taking over the issue, Modol said that, by simplifying the side of the region El Valles de Collserola "can be heard as a park, that of Barcelona, no.".
Modol recalls that there is already a work done by the Patronat of Collserola which "must not be lost," thanking the city for the opportunity to offer his corporation to intervene in this project "from the first time.".
Moreover, he meant that the proximity of the mountain with the city is - except that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubt" whether this looming technique must lead the multidisciplinary teams ("a success," he says) that it is creating: "We, the architects, should only be an instrument.".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, because of the bases of the competition it lack a global vision of Collserola: "It was summoned 16 horizontal competition - he says - in the sense mountain - sea, but there was not a longitudinal reading that way and understands the area as a whole.".
This fact, at least in this case, he has opted to participate in the 16 competition.
In a different way, a project for a doors can shock in the programme and definition with that of the architect of the door.
In his opinion, yes, the mayor should ensure that the band immediately above that of Ronda of Dalt should, in all its extension, an area of equipment that performs a gentle transition between the city and green.
