The Secretary Dionisio Perez Jácome gives discloses the details of the air crash in which has lost his life the Secretary of the Government, Francisco Blake and another seven people
The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) informed that the results highlighted on the accident in which has lost his life the Secretary of Government, Francisco Blake Mora and seven other people, indicate that the helicopter was shocked directly against the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot can try a forced landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Perez Jácome, Secretary of Communications and Transport, said that before the takeoff of the aircraft, the pilot found that climate conditions were adequate to fly.
"The elements that seem to indicate that the unit has had various contacts with the ground the blades have had contact with the trees to 25 yards where the unit has lost the fuselage.".
He informed the fact that the unit was designed to 19 people, therefore it met the requirements needed to transport staff.
Moreover, he said that the investigations made in the area of impact do not report the appearance of parts on the ground.
"In a search has been reported that there was no parts or components of the aircraft in another location, the impact of structural way.
"The helicopter had been designed to 19 passengers and met the requirements for transport.
The ground had a slope of seven to 30 degrees of inclination.
For the moment, the secretary said a priority is to have the results as soon as possible; but the investigation may take a few months, it may even last a year.
In turn, Gilberto López Meyer, director general of Airports and Services Auxiliaires said that the moment of impact, the helicopter to the Presidential Major worked in speed of cruiser and this happened on a bottom-up soft ground.
"This information supports the hypothesis of a normal functioning cruiser at the time of the impact," he said.
During the press conference, the owner of the SCT, Pérez Jácome, has listed six important elements in the investigation:
Flight visually:
According to the aviation standards, the flight was conducted under visual flight rules, which means that the crew must have visibility during the flight and on the ground.
Weather:
The reports in the AICM mentioned adequate conditions at takeoff, and the aircraft has progressed to the boundary zone between City and the state of Mexico there were layers of low cloud cover.
Routes selected:
It is likely that "because of the conditions of cloud cover the crew has sought a height lower and more visibility to the valley of Cuernavaca.
Location of the impact.
The details of the impact and the last recording of the aircraft on the radar coincide, probably before the impact there has been no loss of control or alteration of the trajectory of flight.
Dispersion of the remains of the aircraft in an area reduced:
The information available so far suggests that the impact took place on a trajectory right lateral and.
The model of dispersion of the remains of the aircraft suggests that the helicopter was hit on the ground in conditions of structural integrity.
The was not detected traces of fire or explosion:
In the place of the sinister there was still no trace in the remains of the aircraft of a type of explosion or fire.
The latest results of the investigation indicate that the aircraft had multiple contacts with the ground.
During the work of ground was found pieces of the aircraft at a height of 9 000 200 feet - above the average level of the sea, the soil had a slope that goes for seven dégrées to 30 degrees of inclination.
The photographs show the sequence in which he is possibly thrown out of joint throughout his journey.
The information provides elements that seem to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impactes with the soil.
After careful research in an area further that the place surrounded, around the accident, it has not found disperses parts of the aircraft, which bears the presumption that the impact took place in conditions of structural integrity.
MSS announcement protocol to find the gene for obesity
Social Insurance heads an investigation to discover the gene for obesity in children and young people; this is borne by the IPN
The Mexican Institute of Social Insurance (IMSS) announced he leads an investigation to discover the gene for obesity in children and young people, called yet protocol of obesity in children and adolescents who will have the markers associated with being overweight.
In a statement, the head of the Unit for Investigation Médicale in Biochimie of the Hospital of Spécialités Medical Centre National of the 20th century, Miguel Cruz López, explained that it had formed a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social attend.
This team is supported by specialists and students of third round of the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Investigation and Advanced Study (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
In the investigation are invited to participate the population having or not right, to run in the IMSS sports units participating in Valle of Mexico City, where is the evidence to minors every Saturday from 8: 00 a.m.
He stressed that the protocol has started in the Cuauhtémoc Medicine Unit (Estado de Mexico City Poniente) and from 8 October, the activity is taking place in the Medicine Unit of Nezahualcóyolt (Estado de Mexico City Oriente).
After reaching the goal of getting 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in Medicine Unit Independencia (south of Distrito Federal) and finally in the Morelos Medicine Unit (north of Distrito Federal).
He explained that the purpose of this investigation and that e know the components and the importance of genetics in the development of obesity and identify among children and Mexican youth risk factors to prevent the onset of chronic degenerative diseases.
As we celebrate the 14 November the World Day of the Diabètes, he mentioned that the objective is to meet three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years, with the consent and under the supervision of their parents, for the application of specific questionnaires relating to food.
They will also be requested on their physical activity and their family history of heredity diseases, to avoid the risk factors that trigger health conditions like diabetes or kidney failure.
He detailed that Saturdays we will apply to all participants of anthropométriques measurements (weight, height, circumference of the size), determination of blood pressure, glucose levels, cholesterol, triglycerides and insulin (the genetic and seeks to identify people associated with childhood obesity).
Cruz López reported that this investigation is the result of the concern of health professionals to the alarming weight in the case of minors.
'The health investigations of 1999 and 2006 reported that in just six years there has been a rise in the case of boys, 77 percent in obesity and in the case of girls of 47 percent; in regard to overweight there has been a dramatic increase, pointed out the IMSS specialist.
He said that the justification for the search markers is based in the fact that the country's population is different from other genetic history.
He informed that, on average, have a Mexican 65 percent of heredity US-India, a 30 percent and a five percent African and this condition is reflected in people with diabetes and overweight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity is reflected in the inability to burn excess that consumes energy (calories), which is deposited in the form of fat.
The researcher said that the direct benefit for participants is the full valuation of children, which can detect if they have a degree of overweight or obesity.
He even said that the presence of the folds of dark colour (acanthosis) on the neck and arm before - indicate the probability of developing metabolic changes and even meadow - diabetes.
The information is managed in a way, the doctors call by writing to parents, which explain each of the measures and changes in the style of life that they must do to prevent disease.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: the physical inactivity, which is the lack of physical activity daily, remain most of the day sitting in front of the TV and use of means of transport instead of going off on short distances.
Another issue is the high caloric intake, i.e. the greater consumption of sugar-sweetened beverages, carbohydrates (tamales - block of meat to maize flour wrapped in sheets of corn, bread, pizza, hamburgers etc.) with a high content of fats and proteins and genetic analysis in this protocol.
The asphalt of UNAM would avoid blackcurrants
Rafael Herrera, a researcher from the Faculty of UNAM, equaled the development of asphaltes modified with polymers to produce a mixture with a better performance, regardless of the environmental conditions and temperature
If the know that the streets were resolved, it would not be necessary to fix about 200 000 blackcurrants each season of rain in the Metropolitan Zone of Valle of Mexico City, said Rafael Herrera Nájera, a researcher from the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, who said that if the process of construction and maintenance of the paved sands is adequate, blackcurrants could be reduced or even eliminated completely.
During its conference A technological opinion on the blackcurrants, organised in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, he announced that the laboratory which he is responsible developing asphaltes modified with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of asphalt, but with a greater resistance, both high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera said that this type of asphaltes modified could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some cities in the north of the country, to improve the performance and, therefore, the training of blackcurrants.
He explained that the asphalt, the more heavy oil, is a set of molecules of hydrocarbons, molecules with a higher molecular weight, called asphaltènes, and molecules with a low molecular weight, called malthènes, which together give the paved his characteristic viscoélastique behavior.
The viscoélastique behavior of asphalt is the fact that at high temperatures, nearly 180 degrees, behaves like a liquid, 120 degrees C its viscosity is very large and 50 degrees C it presents an almost solid, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt is slashing, he added.
This means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform and changes during the day depending on the environmental conditions and temperature, the specialist in chemical engineering.
The researcher of the FQ observed that the streets of Ciudad in Mexico City in their majority were covered by a flexible, composed of six layers of materials, including the last three imply the asphalt.
Among the more superficial layers is the layer of asphalt, formed by small stones drenched in asphalt and packed later.
Each small stones that form the layer, he warned, is bathed year asphalt.
When the vehicles spend generating efforts, it allows that the forces spread very well in the streets.
If we had the asphalt amended, those - it will be better, opinât the ingénier chemical.
On the layer of asphalt, he says, is a last layer called layer of turnover, made in stone, i.e., sand that is also bathed in asphalt.
As it is the layer in contact with the wheels of vehicles, it must have more mechanical force that the layer of asphalt and provide grip in the street.
As part of that receives and distributes the efforts, the layer of turnover also requires it to have a proper thickness and the material it is made must be treated.
The climate, especially the humidity and temperature changes, are also a very important factor to consider, especially the water, he says, because those - they affect significantly the performance of the layer of asphalt.
When the ground is, the water spreads inside the layer is that it is difficult, which ramollie all sections of the streets and therefore cause of blackcurrants.
In the trial of training a blackcurrants, he says, the first which is spoiling the film and only later turnover is affected the layer of asphalt, but the injury did not take place immediately, but it is a process that must be treated to the first signs with adequate maintenance programs.
The member of the National System Chercheurs explained that the burden of vehicles is another important factor for the training of blackcurrants and therefore the thickness of each layer of the stone must always be linked to the burden of vehicles and ensure its satisfaction, to avoid the formation of blackcurrants.
Rafael Herrera warned that there was still much to investigate and work on the asphalt emulsions, for example, the bitumineuses, which in other countries are already on the market and help repair the blackcurrants easily and without having to use high temperatures.
