Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A dactyloscopiste of Cali is history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano.
The work of these officials is crucial.
The past November 4, a dactyloscopiste of the Cali ITC has history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the FARC, "Alfonso Cano", by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopistes who work in the local offices of the ITC, this week it was the turn of "availability of Eliazar González, a man of Puerto Tejada who works for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipes of Chocó, where many times he had to spend five days in the forest to reach the place in which were the bodies that were to be identified.
The year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after appropriate courses, he specialized in fingerprinting, which is the study of the skin of friction, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano had been warned to Eliazar to take with him clothes at least for three days.
Something very big expected.
On Friday night is party to Cauca Palmira in a helicopter.
He knew he had to identify two bodies and suspected that one of them was the man who ran the world's oldest guerrilla, therefore asked to take the card with the ten Guillermo León Sáenz fingerprint (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigative team to the location of the body, it has not recognised by his physical aspect, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed as a peasant in the area, without glasses and much more.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a magnifying glass galtonienne, ink sampling, and a lamp, Eliazar has compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye was deceived: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed the Defense Minister Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, it was the supreme leader.
In research footprint
For a dactyloscopiste of Sijín of Cali recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos is to Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano," is very significant.
Many people is not our work.
The fingerprinting is an exact science, no margin of error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
In part to identify bodies, the dactyloscopistes supports the investigation for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of those captured.
When are caught, many have false identity cards or have no documents.
We take their fingerprints and seek in the database.
The researcher told that in a case of theft he had to remove part of a wall of a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to get a boot - very full of jewellery and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to draw a fingerprint, but in this case we have been able to get the footprint of the hand and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
The fingerprints can also rule out or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently we found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
For interlude investigation has determined that a relative can be suspect of the crime and a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if this No guarantees that it is not the killer, that the place on the scene of the crime.
A dactyloscopiste of the ITC said it extracted "fingerprints objects with physical or chemical reagents.".
When they appear, using a sampling or a band for the levy.
In addition, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the data base of offenders, or the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombian," said the expert of the ITC.
He explained that not everything is how it shows in the television programme CSI.
As all that glitters is not gold, all that touches is not necessarily a footprint.
It can be used, if the confrontation is necessary.
