Spain "has reached a prominent place at global level in the role of Micro-finances.".
The Queen Sofía recalled that the country has become in the last two decades the second donor of the planet in relation to this cooperation instrument which "the essence" lies in the fact that it is "an instrument for social progress, justice and hope in a better future for all humanity, based on confidence in the human being.".
The Queen opened yesterday the V - e World Summit on Microcredit in Valladolid with the certainty that there was "no doubt" that such operations are "absolutely essential" to achieve the Millennium Development Goals established by the United Nations for 2015, and, in particular, has as its goal the reduction to half the volume of people with incomes under a dollar a day, which is set the poverty threshold. ".
Spain "continues to work" to expand the network of beneficiaries "in all corners of the planet, and this task with" responsibility, "reported the Queen Sofía, who hoped that the initiatives and contributions origins during the summit, which will last until Thursday," guarantee the creation of new capacities and better opportunities for the poor, and especially for women, "the main beneficiaries of these loans.
We have achieved many objectives "and" we face many challenges. ".
The Microcredit Summit is considered not only as a for debate, but also as the platform from which to spearhead "two basic goals.".
Thus, His Majesty explained that the goal is that at the end of 2015 there has 175 million poor families who have acceded to these financial services and that 100 million of these families out of poverty threshold in which they now live.
The momentum in the design of micro-credits in Spain and in the rest of the world "followed the trail initiated a few years ago in a pioneer" by Muhammad Yunus, said the Queen Sofía as an "act of justice and due recognition.".
And she has described the father of this instrument as an "idealist admirable in the universal cause of the fight against poverty," the work which she has known since 15 years ago, when the Queen has travelled to Bangladesh to get on the ground its lending policy.
This experience was followed a year later by the first World Summit in Washington and other meetings as those held in the Ivory Coast in 1999, Canada in 2006, and "in every meeting I could see a continuing evolution," said His Majesty, whose relationship with this project brought him yesterday the term "head of family" meeting in Valladolid from "as the deep pocket of the poor.".
Finally, the Queen Sofía finished his speech by encouraging people to participate in the debate and in the search for solutions to move forward in the fight against poverty.
