rates go up, the flanchent stock
The risk of contagion of the debt crisis undermines the European indexes.
Despite the appointment of new heads of government in Greece and Italy and better growth figures in France and Germany, rates of the countries affected continue their ascent.
Also worried for the stability of the euro zone, European stock markets are a little more in negative territory on Tuesday November 15.
