Portugal very confident
Portugal's Paulo Bento begins with a lot of optimistic his dam return to Bosnia (2200) on Tuesday in Lisbon.
On the go, both teams had been realistic.
"At the end of the 90 minutes, we will be a happy team and, above all, a country happy.".
Paulo Bento is already sees, in Poland and Ukraine.
For him, it is not the shadow of a doubt, the Selecçao, which it is the levers since September 2010, will qualify for Euro 2012.
Portugal is 90 minutes of happiness.
But there was a game to play, and an opponent, Bosnia, to unseat.
In view of the game go (0-0), Friday in the hell of Zenica, it seems clear that the games are not facts.
Portugal has dominated the party for more than an hour, but he was unable to score that goal so valuable, that would have relieved.
"This is a good result, which contains a certain risk because we have not scored a goal outside"
But at home, in their luminous Stade de la Luz in Lisbon, the Portuguese are convinced to move to a public which should also be steaming, even if the party is "very close" course, Walgreen a Bento optimistic but lucid.
"We expect a very tight game, but we are quite convinced to take over," said the 42-year-old Portuguese coach.
"We continue to have a 50% chance of being at the Euro 2012", has played down the successor to Carlos Queiroz.
The no reported Friday of Bosnia requires the Portuguese to score and win.
A draw may be enough to the Bosnians, who have also need to score.
